This file defines the core types used throughout the DocMed application.

### Key Exports

*   **`ManifestEntry`**: Represents an entry in the documentation manifest, including the file path, display title, and a unique document key.
    ```typescript
    export type ManifestEntry = { filePath: string; title: string; docKey: string };
    ```
*   **`DocFile`**: Represents a single documentation file, containing its file path, title, and its parsed content.
    ```typescript
    export type DocFile = { filePath: string; title: string; content: string };
    ```
*   **`Commit`**: Represents a Git commit, including its ID, message, pusher, and timestamp.
    ```typescript
    export type Commit = { id: string; message: string; pusher: string; timestamp: string };
    ```
*   **`View`**: Defines the different states or views within the application. This is a discriminated union.
    ```typescript
    export type View = {
      type: "home";
    } | {
      type: "commits";
    } | {
      type: "doc";
      key: string;
    } | {
      type: "folder";
      path: string;
    };
    ```
*   **`Tab`**: Represents a tab in the UI, linking a unique ID, a `View`, and a user-facing label.
    ```typescript
    export type Tab = { id: string; view: View; label: string };
    ```

### Usage

These types are fundamental for defining data structures used across the application, such as when processing documentation files, managing application state, or defining navigation elements.
